# Command cspell

## What does this command do:

A Spell Checker for Code

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: `npm install -g --save-dev cspell`
For Raspberry Pi install using:
```bash
curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.40.2/install.sh | bash
source ~/.bashrc
nvm install 22
nvm use 22
npm install -g --save-dev cspell
```
For Mac install using: `brew install cspell`

## Command path

For Fedora run: `/home/kinscoe/.local/bin/cspell`
For Raspberry Pi run: `/home/kinscoe/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.2/bin/cspell`
For Mac run: `cspell`

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://cspell.org/

## Command options

### Top-level commands
    cspell lint [globs...]              Check spelling (default command)
    cspell trace [words...]             Search for words across all dictionaries
    cspell check <files...>             Spell check with full colorized file display
    cspell suggestions [words...]       Show spelling suggestions for words
    cspell init                         Initialize a cspell config file
    cspell link                         Link dictionaries to global config
    cspell dictionaries                 List available dictionaries

### Lint (check spelling)
# Check all files recursively
cspell .
cspell lint .

# Check specific file types
cspell "**/*.md"
cspell "**/*.{ts,js,py}"

# Exclude files or directories
cspell . --exclude "node_modules/**"

# Show only misspelled words (no context)
cspell . --words-only

# Show only first occurrence of each unknown word
cspell . --unique

# Show surrounding context around each issue
cspell . --show-context

# Show spelling suggestions inline
cspell . --show-suggestions

# Use a specific config file
cspell . --config ./cspell.json

# Respect .gitignore files
cspell . --gitignore

# Include hidden dot-files/dirs
cspell . --dot

# Use cache to only recheck changed files
cspell . --cache

# Pipe stdin through cspell
cat file.txt | cspell stdin
echo "helo world" | cspell stdin

# Read from stdin treating it as a specific file type
cat myfile.py | cspell stdin://myfile.py

# Fail fast on first file with issues
cspell . --fail-fast

# Silent mode (suppress all output, use exit code only)
cspell . --silent

# Suppress progress and summary, show issues only
cspell . --quiet

# Force language for unknown extensions
cspell myfile --language-id python

# Set locale
cspell . --locale en-GB

### Trace (dictionary lookup)
# Find which dictionaries contain a word
cspell trace hello
cspell trace helo

# Show all dictionaries (including those without the word)
cspell trace --all hello

# Show only dictionaries that have the word
cspell trace --only-found hello

# Ignore case when tracing
cspell trace --ignore-case Hello

### Suggestions
# Get spelling suggestions for a word
cspell suggestions helllo

# Increase number of suggestions
cspell suggestions helllo --num-suggestions 10

# REPL mode for interactive lookups
cspell suggestions --repl

### Config file (cspell.json / .cspell.json)
# Initialize config
cspell init

# Common config structure
# {
#   "version": "0.2",
#   "language": "en",
#   "words": ["myCustomWord"],
#   "ignorePaths": ["node_modules", "dist"],
#   "ignoreWords": ["someword"],
#   "dictionaries": ["typescript", "node"]
# }

### In-file directives (inline suppression)
# Disable cspell for the whole file (top of file)
# cspell:disable

# Re-enable cspell
# cspell:enable

# Disable next line only
# cspell:disable-next-line
someVariableWithTypo = true

# Add words to the local dictionary inline
# cspell:words myword anotherword

# Ignore specific words inline
# cspell:ignore myword

### Integration examples
# Check only staged files (pre-commit hook)
git diff --cached --name-only | xargs cspell --no-must-find-files

# Check changed files against main
git diff main --name-only | xargs cspell --no-must-find-files

# Use with a file list
cspell --file-list files.txt

# Use a custom reporter (JSON output)
cspell . --reporter @cspell/cspell-json-reporter
